React Aria handles "Grid" in two distinct ways: visual page layout (via React Spectrum’s Grid component) and ARIA grid widgets (via hooks like useGridList or useTable). It provides robust layout structuring and manages complex, focusable data collections with strict accessibility compliance.
Layouts: React Spectrum https://react-spectrum.adobe.com/

React Spectrum is a complete, pre-styled UI component library built entirely to match Adobe's proprietary design system. In contrast, React Aria is a headless (unstyled) library that provides accessible hooks and building blocks, allowing developers to implement their own custom designs, styling, and DOM structures

https://react-aria.adobe.com/blog/introducing-react-spectrum
https://react-spectrum.adobe.com/

